node.text:
⁣Leftover prawn broth from the last post gets repurposed into laksa after a special delivery of homemade laksa paste from @2mamasandawok⠀
⠀
⠀
Just added the paste to the broth and coconut milk and I had a completely new dish. If you've never had laksa with a really good prawn broth... it's really spectacular, the amount of depth the laksa has is incredible, the spice from the laksa paste comes first but the sweet-savory taste of the prawn broth comes after. Waves and waves of flavor 😌
@lennardy Wow, the laksa looks nice, Lennard 😊👍🏻
What a good idea! I shall try it out 👍
Alamak... Cockles cover up but is 🤤🤤🤤
@bettyshanghai I have but I don't eat that too often! From memory it's quite a thick version
Have you ever tried claypot laksa? We tried to find it in Singapore but the one place we found had closed early when we showed up 😭
What a great idea! Love it❤️
@mohdiqbalkarim haha I didn't make this one but they're easy to find online
Laksa 😋 Please share the recipe of laksa paste 🙏🏼

@cyn_thia_ haha I usually just eyeball it. If you want it more soupy add more stock. If you want more creaminess/richness add more coconut. You can try to 'season' with the laksa paste. If there's not enough spice add more paste. Most store bought pastes have salt so be careful with it!
Omg just nice i have some prawn broth leftover. Gonna make this tomorrow! Can i know how much coconut with how much of prawn stock and laksa paste?
@chubbychinesegirleats aw. I'm sure you can make it!
@lennardy I agree 🙌🏻 I can just imagine the umami in this bowl ☺🍲
Sooooo mouthwatering 😍 especially with flavourful prawn broth 😋🙌🏻
@renztan hahah it makes a big diff when you have good stock!
You made me order laksa paste so I can try this loh. Hahaha
